DialogueLine.dialogue: I checked the storage unit just now and noticed that one of the new artifacts went missing. The starry plinth?
Hey Cass, I just noticed that the starry plinth is gone from storage. Any ideas as to where it went?
One of the artifacts was missing! Did you see where it went, by any chance?
An important artifact in next week's exhibit is gone. Have you gone to the storage room recently?
Hey, have you seen the starry plinth anywhere?
Have you seen Director Virgil?
I have to report the missing artifact to the director. Is there... anything I need to know?
I'm going to have to report the missing artifact to the director. Let me know if you learn anything new, okay?
I'm going to go report the missing artifact to the director. I'll be right back.
I've been looking for Director Virgil for a while. Have you seen him by any chance? Cassandra said they talked yesterday afternoon, but that's it...
I need to report that the plinth is gone. If he comes by, let him know I need to see him.
I haven't called him yet. I'll let you know when I do.
Thanks, Jonathan. I'll do that now.
I haven't called him yet...
Called him and it went straight to voice mail.
My call went straight to voice mail. Right when we need him the most, am I right?
Thanks, Jonathan.
Jonathan is letting me use his phone to call the director.
I called the director. It went straight to voice mail...
I called the director and it went straight to voice mail. Do you know where he is?
I think Cassandra did it. What do you think?
I think Jonathan didi it. What do you think
Honestly, I feel like one of the custodians seem suspicious. Don't you think?
{speakerArchetype:assistant} seems awfully stranger than usual. Do you think so too?
Hey, I called Director Virgil with Jonathan's phone and he left me with a voice mail. It's unlike him.
Hey, I called Director Virgil with Jonathan's phone and he left me with a voice mail. Do you know where he is?
So he hasn't contacted you since yesterday? That's really unlike him.
He hasn't contacted you since yesterday? You didn't bother reaching out or looking for him? That's your job.
He hasn't contacted you once? With the plinth missing, you must be losing your mind, then...
What do you think we should do?
What should we do... *visibly panic*
What should we do...
Well. I guess this is your problem now.
Sorry, I was kidding.
I'll... I'll try to get to the bottom of this.
The director is missing! *cry*
Apparently, {speakerArchetype:assistant} isn't able to contact the director today. I need your help to deal with the plinth while he's not here.
Please help me!
Could you help me out?
Oh... can I have them?
Can you help me get into the director's office? To investigate.
"Please! I'm begging you

addEventToGlobal.addEventToGlobalItem: you have to help me out here! Is there anything I can do?!"

DialogueLine.dialogue: Look, my job is on the line too! My family... my life... if this artifact can't be found then why am I here?
Please? Maybe I can return the favor somehow. If we don't find that artifact, all of us will get in trouble.
What if I help you out too? Is there anything I can help you with?
You know the director won't mind if it's an emergency. *This* is an emergency.
I'm sure you won't get in trouble if the director finds out. This is an emergency situation. Wouldn't you like it if he discovers *you* helped *me* find out where it is?
Losing an artifact so close to the exhibit... that's worse than letting me enter his office. Honestly, if you won't help me, you might get into worse trouble.
I'm helping you out too, {assistant}. I... I see that Director Virgil overworks you. And I see that he's harsh on you...
Look, I know the director treats you badly. I frankly have no clue why you're still here but--
I hate to say this, but if he's mean to you now... he might be meaner if you don't help me find this.
You might get in trouble if we don't find this either way. But if we find it... I'll make sure to give you the lion's share of the credit.
